B.P. Kondratyev
Formation of theoretical thought in astronomy
If a researcher wants to understand the exciting process of how the truth is born and how the ancients used to overcome
the difficulties and confusions inevitably accompanying the scientific research, it is best to refer to the segment of sci-
ence history, which begins with the astronomy of the ancient Greeks. All modern science is imbued with Hellenes' in-
spiration. Tracing the genesis of the concepts in the theory of planetary motion, we see that there exists one important
rule: in the history of science, the concept of harmony and beauty is not something frozen, it is developed and renewed
in the process of learning of the World. Thus, in nearly twenty centuries, the naive ideas of the ancient Greeks about a
uniform and ideally circular motion of planets are replaced with the Kepler's ellipses. It would seem that these ellipses
violate all notions of harmony in the Universe but they actually represent a new level of harmony that transcends the old
one. In the second part we consider the formation and development of potential theory, which plays an important role in
modern Celestial mechanics.
Keywords: astronomy, history of the development, theory of the cognition, ancient greeks, Renaissance, celestial
mechanics, potential theory.
Кондратьев Борис Петрович,
доктор физико-математических наук, профессор
